Fix Authoring editor: populate textarea from stored content, not the textarea

Bug: the New Skill template never prefilled, and switching an existing
prompt/skill to Edit blanked it. Cause: entering Edit set the textarea's value
from liveContent(), which read the *just-created empty* #auText element and
returned "" instead of the intended content.

Fix: wireTabs() now manages a single source of truth (state.content). Entering
Edit fills the textarea FROM state.content; switching to Preview / saving calls
sync() to copy the textarea value BACK into state.content first. Callers
(openPrompt/openSkill/openSkillCreate) pass a state object and sync() before
PUT. So "+ New Skill" prefills the SKILL.md scaffold (valid frontmatter) and
edits are preserved across the Preview/Edit toggle.

Verified: dashboard build clean; npm test green (34 unit + API + smoke).
